705175f-a.title: Brooklyn: Kane Street - Clinton Street
705175f-a.text:
Eane Street, south side, east from Clinton Street to Court
Street. At Tompkins Place is Beth Israel Synagogue.
October 15, 1940
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRCDUCTIONS
705175f-a.folder: Kane Street & Clinton Street, Brooklyn, NY

703683f-c.title: Brooklyn: Clinton Street - Kane Street
703683f-c.text:
Clinton Street, st the S.W. corner of Kane Street,
showing the Christ Protestant Episcopal Church. The
cornerstone was laid in 1842. Nichard Upjohn is the
architect. For additional cata see 'The New York Times,''
February 26, 1939.
On the right is Kane Street, viewing westward.
View 3 is east on Eane Street from Strong Place.
View 1: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection October, 1928
MAY BE REPRODUCED
Views 2,3: P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS  View 2: August 5, 1934
View 3: October 15, 1940
